Oracle Corp. Japan  dropped the
most in almost two years in Tokyo trading after first-quarter
profit declined and the company cut its full-year net income
forecast by 8.2 percent.  The Japanese unit of software maker Oracle Corp. fell
8.3 percent to 4,080 yen as of 10:17 a.m. on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange, headed for the biggest decline since October 2008.
The stock was the worst performer on the  MSCI World Index .
Japanâ€™s benchmark Topix index lost 0.9 percent.  Oracle Japan reported a 6.7 percent drop in quarterly
net income and lowered its profit projection for the year
ending May to 22.4 billion yen ($265 million), in separate
statements to the Tokyo Stock Exchange after the close of
trading on Sept. 22. Japanese financial markets were closed
yesterday for a holiday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
